    {"Equipment": "Dumbbell", "Muscle": "Back", "Exercise": "Renegade Row", "Instructions": "Begin in a plank position with a dumbbell in each hand. Row one dumbbell towards your torso while stabilizing with the other hand. Alternate rows while engaging your core to prevent rotation. This exercise strengthens the upper back and core."},
    {"Equipment": "Dumbbell", "Muscle": "Chest", "Exercise": "Dumbbell Bench Press", "Instructions": "Lie on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand. Press the dumbbells straight up, keeping your elbows at a 45-degree angle. Lower the dumbbells back to chest level. This exercise targets the chest, shoulders, and triceps."},
