    {"Equipment": "Dumbbell", "Muscle": "Shoulders", "Exercise": "Dumbbell Shoulder Press", "Instructions": "Sit or stand with a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height. Press the dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended. Lower them back down with control. This exercise targets the shoulders and triceps."},
    {"Equipment": "Dumbbell", "Muscle": "Shoulders", "Exercise": "Lateral Raise", "Instructions": "Stand with a dumbbell in each hand by your sides. Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, then lower back down. This exercise targets the shoulders, particularly the lateral deltoids."},
    {"Equipment": "Dumbbell", "Muscle": "Shoulders", "Exercise": "Front Raise", "Instructions": "Stand with a dumbbell in each hand by your sides. Raise the dumbbells in front of you until your arms are parallel to the floor, then lower back down. This exercise targets the front deltoids."},
    {"Equipment": "Dumbbell", "Muscle": "Shoulders", "Exercise": "Arnold Press", "Instructions": "Sit or stand with a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height. Rotate your palms toward your body and press the dumbbells overhead while rotating your palms outward. Lower the dumbbells back down with control. This variation of the shoulder press targets all parts of the deltoids."},
    {"Equipment": "Dumbbell", "Muscle": "Biceps", "Exercise": "Dumbbell Curl", "Instructions": "Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. Curl the dumbbells toward your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your torso. Squeeze your biceps at the top, then lower the dumbbells back down. This exercise isolates the biceps."},
    {"Equipment": "Dumbbell", "Muscle": "Biceps", "Exercise": "Hammer Curl", "Instructions": "Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. Curl the dumbbells toward your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your torso. Lower the dumbbells back down. This exercise targets the brachialis and forearms, in addition to the biceps."},
    {"Equipment": "Dumbbell", "Muscle": "Biceps", "Exercise": "Concentration Curl", "Instructions": "Sit on a bench with your legs spread apart. Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your elbow resting on your inner thigh. Curl the dumbbell toward your shoulder, squeezing your biceps at the top. Lower it back down with control. This exercise isolates the biceps for a more concentrated contraction."},
