    {"Equipment": "Pull-up Bar", "Muscle": "Back", "Exercise": "Lat Pulldown", "Instructions": "Sit at a lat pulldown machine with a wide grip on the bar. Pull the bar down toward your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together at the bottom of the movement. Slowly return the bar to the starting position. This exercise targets the lats and upper back."},
    {"Equipment": "Pull-up Bar", "Muscle": "Shoulders", "Exercise": "Pull-up", "Instructions": "Grip the pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you. Hang with your arms fully extended, then pull your chest up toward the bar. Lower your body back down with control. This exercise targets the shoulders, traps, lats, and biceps."},
    {"Equipment": "Resistance Bands", "Muscle": "Full Body", "Exercise": "Band Squat", "Instructions": "Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handles of the resistance band with both hands. Position the band under your feet and hold the handles at shoulder height. Squat down, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. Push through your heels to stand back up. This exercise targets the quads, hamstrings, and glutes."},
